1681  gtid, parent_team->t.t_id, parent_team->t.t_pkfn ) );
1682  KMP_MB(); /* Flush all pending memory write invalidates. */
1683 
1684  KA_TRACE( 20, ("__kmp_fork_call: parallel exit T#%d\n", gtid ));
1685 
1686  return TRUE;
1687  } // Parallel closely nested in teams construct
1688 #endif /* OMP_40_ENABLED */
1689 
1690 #if KMP_DEBUG
1691  if ( __kmp_tasking_mode != tskm_immediate_exec ) {
1692  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(master_th->th.th_task_team == parent_team->t.t_task_team[master_th->th.th_task_state]);
1693  }
1694 #endif
1695 
1696  if ( parent_team->t.t_active_level >= master_th->th.th_current_task->td_icvs.max_active_levels ) {
1697  nthreads = 1;
1698  } else {
1699 #if OMP_40_ENABLED
1700  int enter_teams = ((ap==NULL && active_level==0)||(ap && teams_level>0 && teams_level==level));
1701 #endif
1702  nthreads = master_set_numthreads ?
1703  master_set_numthreads : get__nproc_2( parent_team, master_tid ); // TODO: get nproc directly from current task
1704 
1705  // Check if we need to take forkjoin lock? (no need for serialized parallel out of teams construct).
1706  // This code moved here from __kmp_reserve_threads() to speedup nested serialized parallels.
1707  if (nthreads > 1) {
1708  if ( ( !get__nested(master_th) && (root->r.r_in_parallel
1709 #if OMP_40_ENABLED
1710  && !enter_teams
1711 #endif /* OMP_40_ENABLED */
1712  ) ) || ( __kmp_library == library_serial ) ) {
1713  KC_TRACE( 10, ( "__kmp_fork_call: T#%d serializing team; requested %d threads\n",
1714  gtid, nthreads ));
1715  nthreads = 1;
1716  }
1717  }
1718  if ( nthreads > 1 ) {
1719  /* determine how many new threads we can use */
1720  __kmp_acquire_bootstrap_lock( &__kmp_forkjoin_lock );
1721 
1722  nthreads = __kmp_reserve_threads(root, parent_team, master_tid, nthreads
1723 #if OMP_40_ENABLED
1724 /* AC: If we execute teams from parallel region (on host), then teams should be created
1725  but each can only have 1 thread if nesting is disabled. If teams called from serial region,
1726  then teams and their threads should be created regardless of the nesting setting. */
1727  , enter_teams
1728 #endif /* OMP_40_ENABLED */
1729  );
1730  if ( nthreads == 1 ) {
1731  // Free lock for single thread execution here;
1732  // for multi-thread execution it will be freed later
1733  // after team of threads created and initialized
1734  __kmp_release_bootstrap_lock( &__kmp_forkjoin_lock );
1735  }
1736  }
1737  }
1738  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT( nthreads > 0 );
1739 
1740  /* If we temporarily changed the set number of threads then restore it now */
1741  master_th->th.th_set_nproc = 0;
1742 
1743  /* create a serialized parallel region? */
1744  if ( nthreads == 1 ) {
1745  /* josh todo: hypothetical question: what do we do for OS X*? */
1746 #if KMP_OS_LINUX && ( KMP_ARCH_X86 || KMP_ARCH_X86_64 || KMP_ARCH_ARM || KMP_ARCH_AARCH64)
1747  void * args[ argc ];
1748 #else
1749  void * * args = (void**) KMP_ALLOCA( argc * sizeof( void * ) );
1750 #endif /* KMP_OS_LINUX && ( KMP_ARCH_X86 || KMP_ARCH_X86_64 || KMP_ARCH_ARM || KMP_ARCH_AARCH64) */
1751 
1752  KA_TRACE( 20, ("__kmp_fork_call: T#%d serializing parallel region\n", gtid ));
1753 
1754  __kmpc_serialized_parallel(loc, gtid);
1755 
1756  if ( call_context == fork_context_intel ) {
1757  /* TODO this sucks, use the compiler itself to pass args! :) */
1758  master_th->th.th_serial_team->t.t_ident = loc;
1759 #if OMP_40_ENABLED
1760  if ( !ap ) {
1761  // revert change made in __kmpc_serialized_parallel()
1762  master_th->th.th_serial_team->t.t_level--;
1763  // Get args from parent team for teams construct
1764 
1765 #if OMPT_SUPPORT
1766  void *dummy;
1767  void **exit_runtime_p;
1768 
1769  ompt_lw_taskteam_t lw_taskteam;
1770 
1771  if (ompt_enabled) {
1772  __ompt_lw_taskteam_init(&lw_taskteam, master_th, gtid,
1773  unwrapped_task, ompt_parallel_id);

1797 #if OMPT_SUPPORT
1798  , exit_runtime_p
1799 #endif
1800  );

1817

1820  ompt_parallel_id, ompt_task_id,
1821  OMPT_INVOKER(call_context));
1822  }

1825 #endif

1827  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT( master_th->th.th_team == master_th->th.th_serial_team );

1835  for( i=argc-1; i >= 0; --i )

1839 # else
1840  *argv++ = va_arg( ap, void * );

1849  team->t.t_level--;

1851  {
1852  KMP_TIME_BLOCK(OMP_work);
1853  invoker(gtid);
1854  }
1855  } else {
1856 #endif /* OMP_40_ENABLED */

1858  for( i=argc-1; i >= 0; --i )
1859 // TODO: revert workaround for Intel(R) 64 tracker #96
1860 #if (KMP_ARCH_X86_64 || KMP_ARCH_ARM || KMP_ARCH_AARCH64) && KMP_OS_LINUX
1861  *argv++ = va_arg( *ap, void * );
1862 #else
1863  *argv++ = va_arg( ap, void * );
1864 #endif
1865  KMP_MB();
1866 
1867 #if OMPT_SUPPORT
1868  void *dummy;
1869  void **exit_runtime_p;
1870

1903 #endif

1924  ompt_parallel_id, ompt_task_id,

1926  }

1928  }
1929 #endif

1931  }
1932 #endif /* OMP_40_ENABLED */

1948  return FALSE;
1949  }

1952  }
1953 
1954 
1955  KA_TRACE( 20, ("__kmp_fork_call: T#%d serial exit\n", gtid ));
1956  KMP_MB();
1957  return FALSE;
1958  }

1960  // GEH: only modify the executing flag in the case when not serialized
1961  // serialized case is handled in kmpc_serialized_parallel
1962  KF_TRACE( 10, ( "__kmp_fork_call: parent_team_aclevel=%d, master_th=%p, curtask=%p, curtask_max_aclevel=%d\n",
1963  parent_team->t.t_active_level, master_th, master_th->th.th_current_task,
1964  master_th->th.th_current_task->td_icvs.max_active_levels ) );

1966  // KMP_ASSERT( master_th->th.th_current_task->td_flags.executing == 1 );
1967  master_th->th.th_current_task->td_flags.executing = 0;
1968 
1969 #if OMP_40_ENABLED
1970  if ( !master_th->th.th_teams_microtask || level > teams_level )
1971 #endif /* OMP_40_ENABLED */
1972  {
1973  /* Increment our nested depth level */
1974  KMP_TEST_THEN_INC32( (kmp_int32*) &root->r.r_in_parallel );
1975  }

1977  // See if we need to make a copy of the ICVs.
1978  int nthreads_icv = master_th->th.th_current_task->td_icvs.nproc;
1979  if ((level+1 < __kmp_nested_nth.used) && (__kmp_nested_nth.nth[level+1] != nthreads_icv)) {
1980  nthreads_icv = __kmp_nested_nth.nth[level+1];
1981  }
1982  else {
1983  nthreads_icv = 0; // don't update
1984  }
1985 
1986 #if OMP_40_ENABLED

1988  kmp_proc_bind_t proc_bind = master_th->th.th_set_proc_bind;

1990  if ( master_th->th.th_current_task->td_icvs.proc_bind == proc_bind_false ) {
1991  proc_bind = proc_bind_false;
1992  }
1993  else {
1994  if (proc_bind == proc_bind_default) {
1995  // No proc_bind clause specified; use current proc-bind-var for this parallel region
1996  proc_bind = master_th->th.th_current_task->td_icvs.proc_bind;
1997  }
1998  /* else: The proc_bind policy was specified explicitly on parallel clause. This
1999  overrides proc-bind-var for this parallel region, but does not change proc-bind-var. */
2000  // Figure the value of proc-bind-var for the child threads.
2001  if ((level+1 < __kmp_nested_proc_bind.used)
2002  && (__kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[level+1] != master_th->th.th_current_task->td_icvs.proc_bind)) {
2003  proc_bind_icv = __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[level+1];
2004  }
2005  }
2006 
2007  // Reset for next parallel region
2008  master_th->th.th_set_proc_bind = proc_bind_default;
2009 #endif /* OMP_40_ENABLED */
2010 
2011  if ((nthreads_icv > 0)
2012 #if OMP_40_ENABLED
2013  || (proc_bind_icv != proc_bind_default)
2014 #endif /* OMP_40_ENABLED */
2015  ) {
2016  kmp_internal_control_t new_icvs;
2017  copy_icvs(&new_icvs, &master_th->th.th_current_task->td_icvs);
2018  new_icvs.next = NULL;
2019  if (nthreads_icv > 0) {
2020  new_icvs.nproc = nthreads_icv;
2021  }
2022 
2023 #if OMP_40_ENABLED
2024  if (proc_bind_icv != proc_bind_default) {
2025  new_icvs.proc_bind = proc_bind_icv;
2026  }
2027 #endif /* OMP_40_ENABLED */
2028 
2029  /* allocate a new parallel team */
2030  KF_TRACE( 10, ( "__kmp_fork_call: before __kmp_allocate_team\n" ) );
2031  team = __kmp_allocate_team(root, nthreads, nthreads,
2032 #if OMPT_SUPPORT
2033  ompt_parallel_id,
2034 #endif
2035 #if OMP_40_ENABLED
2036  proc_bind,
2037 #endif
2038  &new_icvs, argc USE_NESTED_HOT_ARG(master_th) );
2039  } else {
2040  /* allocate a new parallel team */
2041  KF_TRACE( 10, ( "__kmp_fork_call: before __kmp_allocate_team\n" ) );
2042  team = __kmp_allocate_team(root, nthreads, nthreads,
2043 #if OMPT_SUPPORT
2044  ompt_parallel_id,
2045 #endif

2055  team->t.t_master_tid = master_tid;
2056  team->t.t_master_this_cons = master_this_cons;

2058  team->t.t_parent = parent_team;

2062 #endif

2065 #if OMP_40_ENABLED

2067 #endif /* OMP_40_ENABLED */

2069  team->t.t_active_level = parent_team->t.t_active_level + 1;
2070 #if OMP_40_ENABLED
2071  } else {
2072  // AC: Do not increase parallel level at start of the teams construct
2073  team->t.t_level = parent_team->t.t_level;
2074  team->t.t_active_level = parent_team->t.t_active_level;
2075  }
2076 #endif /* OMP_40_ENABLED */
2077  team->t.t_sched = get__sched_2(parent_team, master_tid); // set master's schedule as new run-time schedule
2078

2080  team->t.t_cancel_request = cancel_noreq;
2081 #endif
2082 
2083  // Update the floating point rounding in the team if required.
2084  propagateFPControl(team);
2085 
2086  if ( __kmp_tasking_mode != tskm_immediate_exec ) {
2087  // Set master's task team to team's task team. Unless this is hot team, it should be NULL.
2088 #if 0
2089  // Patch out an assertion that trips while the runtime seems to operate correctly.
2090  // Avoiding the preconditions that cause the assertion to trip has been promised as a forthcoming patch.
2091  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(master_th->th.th_task_team == parent_team->t.t_task_team[master_th->th.th_task_state]);
2092 #endif

2094  __kmp_gtid_from_thread( master_th ), master_th->th.th_task_team,
2095  parent_team, team->t.t_task_team[master_th->th.th_task_state], team ) );
2096 
2097  if ( level || master_th->th.th_task_team ) {
2098  // Take a memo of master's task_state
2099  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(master_th->th.th_task_state_memo_stack);
2100  if (master_th->th.th_task_state_top >= master_th->th.th_task_state_stack_sz) { // increase size
2101  kmp_uint32 new_size = 2*master_th->th.th_task_state_stack_sz;
2102  kmp_uint8 *old_stack, *new_stack;
2103  kmp_uint32 i;
2104  new_stack = (kmp_uint8 *)__kmp_allocate(new_size);
2105  for (i=0; i<master_th->th.th_task_state_stack_sz; ++i) {
2106  new_stack[i] = master_th->th.th_task_state_memo_stack[i];
2107  }
2108  for (i=master_th->th.th_task_state_stack_sz; i<new_size; ++i) { // zero-init rest of stack
2109  new_stack[i] = 0;
2110  }
2111  old_stack = master_th->th.th_task_state_memo_stack;
2112  master_th->th.th_task_state_memo_stack = new_stack;
2113  master_th->th.th_task_state_stack_sz = new_size;
2114  __kmp_free(old_stack);
2115  }
2116  // Store master's task_state on stack
2117  master_th->th.th_task_state_memo_stack[master_th->th.th_task_state_top] = master_th->th.th_task_state;
2118  master_th->th.th_task_state_top++;
2119 #if KMP_NESTED_HOT_TEAMS
2120  if (team == master_th->th.th_hot_teams[level].hot_team) { // Restore master's nested state if nested hot team
2121  master_th->th.th_task_state = master_th->th.th_task_state_memo_stack[master_th->th.th_task_state_top];
2122  }
2123  else {
2124 #endif
2125  master_th->th.th_task_state = 0;
2126 #if KMP_NESTED_HOT_TEAMS
2127  }
2128 #endif
2129  }
2130 #if !KMP_NESTED_HOT_TEAMS
2131  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT((master_th->th.th_task_team == NULL) || (team == root->r.r_hot_team));
2132 #endif
2133  }
2134 
2135  KA_TRACE( 20, ("__kmp_fork_call: T#%d(%d:%d)->(%d:0) created a team of %d threads\n",
2136  gtid, parent_team->t.t_id, team->t.t_master_tid, team->t.t_id, team->t.t_nproc ));
2137  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT( team != root->r.r_hot_team ||
2138  ( team->t.t_master_tid == 0 &&
2139  ( team->t.t_parent == root->r.r_root_team || team->t.t_parent->t.t_serialized ) ));
2140  KMP_MB();
2141 
2142  /* now, setup the arguments */
2143  argv = (void**)team->t.t_argv;
2144 #if OMP_40_ENABLED
2145  if ( ap ) {
2146 #endif /* OMP_40_ENABLED */
2147  for ( i=argc-1; i >= 0; --i )
2148 // TODO: revert workaround for Intel(R) 64 tracker #96
2149 #if (KMP_ARCH_X86_64 || KMP_ARCH_ARM || KMP_ARCH_AARCH64) && KMP_OS_LINUX
2150  *argv++ = va_arg( *ap, void * );
2151 #else
2152  *argv++ = va_arg( ap, void * );
2153 #endif
2154 #if OMP_40_ENABLED
2155  } else {
2156  for ( i=0; i < argc; ++i )
2157  // Get args from parent team for teams construct
2158  argv[i] = team->t.t_parent->t.t_argv[i];
2159  }
2160 #endif /* OMP_40_ENABLED */
2161

5665  KA_TRACE( 30, ( "__kmp_internal_end_atexit\n" ) );
5666  /* [Windows]
5667  josh: ideally, we want to completely shutdown the library in this atexit handler, but
5668  stat code that depends on thread specific data for gtid fails because that data becomes
5669  unavailable at some point during the shutdown, so we call __kmp_internal_end_thread
5670  instead. We should eventually remove the dependency on __kmp_get_specific_gtid in the
5671  stat code and use __kmp_internal_end_library to cleanly shutdown the library.
5672 
5673 // TODO: Can some of this comment about GVS be removed?
5674  I suspect that the offending stat code is executed when the calling thread tries to
5675  clean up a dead root thread's data structures, resulting in GVS code trying to close
5676  the GVS structures for that thread, but since the stat code uses
5677  __kmp_get_specific_gtid to get the gtid with the assumption that the calling thread is
5678  cleaning up itself instead of another thread, it gets confused. This happens because
5679  allowing a thread to unregister and cleanup another thread is a recent modification for
5680  addressing an issue with Maxon Cinema4D. Based on the current design (20050722), a
5681  thread may end up trying to unregister another thread only if thread death does not
5682  trigger the calling of __kmp_internal_end_thread. For Linux* OS, there is the thread
5683  specific data destructor function to detect thread death. For Windows dynamic, there
5684  is DllMain(THREAD_DETACH). For Windows static, there is nothing. Thus, the
5685  workaround is applicable only for Windows static stat library.
5686  */
5687  __kmp_internal_end_library( -1 );
5688  #if KMP_OS_WINDOWS
5689  __kmp_close_console();
5690  #endif
